REQUIREMENTS:
- labels: one entry per destination above, {"to": N, "label": "..."}.
- A label is the player's voice: a concrete present-tense action, no outcomes
  revealed. No meta-language — "continue", "go to the next scene" are failures;
  even a single onward choice deserves a diegetic line.
- Labels leaving this passage must differ from one another.
- Match the tone. Never mention flags, dilemmas, or structure in a label.
{% if is_rendering %}
- THIS PASSAGE is one rendering of a cosmetic fork, rejoining a road the reader
  could have walked plainly. Its rejoin label must voice THIS rendering's
  residue — the mood, image, or small knowing the reader now carries — so it
  reads differently from simply walking on. Never re-offer an action a parallel
  passage already labels onto the same destination (marked ALREADY OFFERED
  above): same road reached, a different memory of reaching it.
{% endif %}
